extends layout.pug

block content 
  nav.grid-container.portfolio-breadcrumb
    a(href='/') ← Back
  article.grid-container.portfolio-intro.portfolio-project
    .grid-x
      .cell.small-6.medium-9.large-9

        //- Add your name.
        h1 Luis Giraldo

        //- Feel free personalize the title below
        p.lead.text-light
          | Full Stack JavaScript Developer.

        //- Replace the boilerplate below with your Elevator pitch below.
        .portfolio-bio
          p
            | Hi! my name is Luis Giraldo a Full Stack Web Developer, passionate about coding, problem solving, playing with layouts using imagination, and very dedicated to my work. Currently making a better version of myself.
            | When you don't see me coding, you can find me working out, reading a book or hiding in a relaxing place to meditate.
            br
            |I know you can find something that you like from this portfolio, so let's work together!
      .cell.portfolio-meta.small-6.medium-2.large-3
        h6 Skills

        //- Replace the text in the li tags below with your own skills.  At this point, you should be able to list at least ten skills.
        ul
          li HTML
          li CSS
          li JavaScript
          li PHP
          li Node JS 
          li Express
          li Problem Solver
        h6 Contact Info

        //- Add your own contact info
        ul
          li 561-460-7392
          li lugirva@gmail.com

        //- Add URLs to the hrefs below to link to your social media accounts.
        a.button.expanded(href='https://www.linkedin.com/in/luisgiraldov/') LinkedIn
        a.button.expanded(href='https://github.com/luisgiraldov') GitHub
        a.button.expanded(href='#') Twitter

    h2(class="center-title") See how my journey started!
    .timeline-container
      .left.text-wrapper
        .text
          h3 Apr 17 2002
          p First Time interacting with a computer, and that day I found my passion for computers
      .right.text-wrapper
        .text
          h3 Jun 23 2012
          p I decided to pursue a career on computers
      .left.text-wrapper
        .text
          h3 Aug 27 2012
          p I started an Associates in Information Technology
      .right.text-wrapper
        .text
          h3 Oct 7 2012
          p First time interacting with code, at that time I wrote my first code, the famous Hello World in Java. That day I discovered my future was in code
      .left.text-wrapper
        .text
          h3 Jan 10 2013
          p I get my first internship as Help Desk technician in Carvajal Tecnologia y Servicios, Colombia
      .right.text-wrapper
        .text
          h3 Oct 27 2013
          p I got accepted as Help Desk Technician in Tecnoquimicas S.A, Colombia
      .left.text-wrapper
        .text
          h3 Jul 5 2014
          p Moved to United States Of America
      .right.text-wrapper
        .text
          h3 Mar 14 2016
          p It was time to return to code, I started practicing Java and JavaScript. Learning from books and mostly youtube tutorials
      .left.text-wrapper
        .text
          h3 Jan 1 2018
          p Started my journey on team treehouse to learn how to be a web developer. This was a life changing situation, they guided me to the right path, and helped me to decide which languages I had to stick to and not jumping around.
      .right.text-wrapper
        .text
          h3 Nov 12 2019
          p I found an amazing opportunity on treehouse, called TalentPath, this was one in a lifetime opportunity. A company was going to pay for my techdegree in FullStack JavaScript, and after graduating they would give me a chance to work 3 months (apprentinceship) in the same company.
      .left.text-wrapper
        .text
          h3 Dec 19 2019
          p I get accepted in the program
      .right.text-wrapper
        .text
          h3 Feb 4 2020
          p Launch of the program, I get to meet people from the company, and get to know the company's facilities. That was the first day of my journey to become a Fullstack Developer
      .left.text-wrapper
        .text
          h3 Mar 4 2020 (Not exact date)
          p COVID-19 came along
      .right.text-wrapper
        .text
          h3 Apr 16 2020
          p Apprenticeship canceled Due to COVID-19, Not enough money to hire new employees
      .left.text-wrapper
        .text
          h3 Apr 22 2020
          p Looking for an opportunity as a Junior Web Developer, not doing it for money but for pursuing dreams, going after passion!
